version_description: Chords for the song 'Wish You Were Here' from Neck Deep's latest album 'The Peace And The Panic'. Interpreted by ear and fit when playing along to the song, but these chords actually being correct isn't guaranteed.

Simple easy to play chords for beginners to follow along with easily. If the F#m is too difficult, a slightly easier version of it to play is xx3111. For C#m you can do 0212xx or xx212x. Whichever feels more comfortable.

I haven't been able to source a video of this, but have had a shot at figuring it out by ear, so see what you think. The trickiest part is the time signature, which is 7/4 for much of the song. I've offered a suggestion for the strumming pattern, but have a listen for yourself and play around with it to find what feels most natural. Capo is on the second fret for the studio version.
Pure chord version of the song, in original key.
